## 3. Incident Classification

| Severity | Definition | Examples | Response Time |
|----------|-----------|----------|---------------|
| **P1 — Critical** | Active exploitation, data breach, or total service outage | Unauthorized data access, malware infection, site defacement | Immediate (within 1 hour) |
| **P2 — High** | Vulnerability being actively exploited or significant service degradation | Exposed credentials, partial outage, suspicious access patterns | Within 4 hours |
| **P3 — Medium** | Vulnerability discovered but no evidence of exploitation | New CVE in dependencies, misconfiguration found, failed login spikes | Within 24 hours |
| **P4 — Low** | Minor security concern, no immediate risk | Outdated dependency, minor policy gap, informational finding | Within 1 week |

