## 7. Containment

### 7.1 Short-Term Containment (Stop the Bleeding)

**P1/P2 — Immediate actions:**

```bash
# Take the site offline if actively compromised
# Option 1: Stop the application
ssh user@server "pm2 stop all"  # or systemctl stop your-app

# Option 2: Block all traffic via firewall
ssh user@server "ufw deny from any to any"

# Option 3: Put up a maintenance page
# (configure in nginx/reverse proxy)
```

**If credentials are compromised:**
```bash
# Rotate all secrets immediately
# 1. Generate new API keys for all services
# 2. Update .env on server
# 3. Revoke old keys in each service dashboard
# 4. Force-reset any user sessions
```

### 7.2 Long-Term Containment

- [ ] Isolate affected systems
- [ ] Preserve evidence (logs, snapshots)
- [ ] Apply temporary fixes (patches, firewall rules)
- [ ] Monitor for continued activity

---

## 8. Eradication

- [ ] Identify root cause
- [ ] Remove malware/unauthorized access
- [ ] Patch vulnerabilities
- [ ] Update dependencies (`npm audit fix`)
- [ ] Rotate all credentials if compromise is confirmed
- [ ] Review and harden security headers
- [ ] Run full GRC scan to verify fixes

---

## 9. Recovery

- [ ] Restore from known-good backup if needed
- [ ] Redeploy application from clean source
- [ ] Verify all services are functioning
- [ ] Run GRC scan to confirm compliance posture
- [ ] Monitor closely for 48-72 hours post-recovery
- [ ] Gradually restore normal operations

---

## 10. Post-Incident

### 10.1 Lessons Learned (within 5 business days)

Document:
- [ ] Timeline of events
- [ ] What went well
- [ ] What could be improved
- [ ] Root cause analysis
- [ ] Action items with owners and deadlines

### 10.2 Regulatory Notification

{{#if (hasGdpr config.jurisdiction)}}
**GDPR (if EU user data was affected):**
- Notify supervisory authority within **72 hours** of becoming aware of a breach (Art. 33)
- Notify affected users "without undue delay" if high risk to their rights (Art. 34)
- Document: nature of breach, categories of data, approximate number of users, consequences, measures taken
{{/if}}

{{#if (hasCcpa config.jurisdiction)}}
**CCPA (if California resident data was affected):**
- Notify affected consumers if unencrypted personal information was breached
- Notification must include: what happened, what data was involved, what you're doing about it
{{/if}}

### 10.3 Update This Plan

After every incident, update this IRP with:
- New detection methods discovered
- Improved containment procedures
- Updated contact information
- New systems or services added to scope
